description.narrative: Digitization of health services was critical in;2020 following the COVID-19 outbreak: virtual;shared medical consultations allowed for;all pregnant women to access ANC services, a communication platform for rural PHC doctors was initiated to allow for sharing of information, training materials and monitoring to support the COVID-19 response, online consultations allowed for adolescent to access psycho-social support and the Birth Registry was enhanced to generate real-time analyses of perinatal field performance. | Status:Met | As-of Date:14/12/2020

title.narrative: Fieldwork for the study of lead exposure sources including lab testing of environmental samples completed (68077)

baseline.value: No data on sources of lead exposure

target.value: 2020:Fieldwork conducted in at least 40 households and surrounding areas of MICS Lead Module participant children with at least 400 different environmental and product specimens analysed

actual.value: 2020:Study of lead exposure sources were conducted via lab testing of lead particles found in children's blood on stable isotopic ratios, as well as GIS and other methods
